Hawaiian Telcom Holdco, Inc. (NASDAQ:HCOM) Downgraded by Sidoti to Neutral

Roana De Caro |
Miércoles, Julio 26, 2017







(NASDAQ:HCOM) by 6.8% during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). 97,461 shares of the company traded hands. Hawaiian Telcom Holdco, Inc. shares had a trading volume of 262K by the end of trading on Friday. We will contrast the two companies based on the strength of their earnings, risk, profitabiliy, valuation, dividends, institutional ownership and analyst recommendations. JPMorgan Chase & Co. boosted its stake in shares of Hawaiian Telcom Holdco by 44.0% in the first quarter. North Star Investment Management Corp. now owns 108,550 shares of the utilities provider's stock worth $2,487,000 after buying an additional 20,900 shares during the period.Analyst Recommendations This is a breakdown of current ratings and recommmendations for VimpelCom and Hawaiian Telcom Holdco, as reported by MarketBeat. Teachers Advisors LLC raised its position in Hawaiian Telcom Holdco by 18.5% in the fourth quarter. State Street Corp now owns 186,241 shares of the utilities provider's stock valued at $4,612,000 after buying an additional 6,767 shares in the last quarter. Sei Investments Co. boosted its stake in shares of Hawaiian Telcom Holdco by 5.2% in the first quarter. JPMorgan Chase & Co. now owns 13,956 shares of the utilities provider's stock worth $320,000 after buying an additional 4,264 shares during the last quarter. Institutional investors and hedge funds own 69.09% of the company's stock. The value of the investment in Hawaiian Telcom Holdco, Inc. increased from $2,487,000 to $2,883,000 increasing 15.9% since the last quarter.
The stock increased 0.10% or $0.03 during the last trading session, reaching $29.15. Hawaiian Telcom Holdco, Inc. The 50 day moving average moved up $3.13 whereas the 200 day moving average was up $4.26 or +17.13%. The company has market cap of $338.84 million.News articles about Hawaiian Telcom Holdco (NASDAQ:HCOM) have trended somewhat positive recently, Accern reports. The utilities provider reported ($0.17) earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing the consensus estimate of $0.02 by $0.19. The company had revenue of $94.51 million during the quarter.Hawaiian Telcom Holdco, Inc., launched on May 19, 2004, is a provider of communications services and products in Hawaii.Wells Fargo & Company MN held its stake in shares of Hawaiian Telcom Holdco, Inc.COPYRIGHT VIOLATION NOTICE: This piece was published by StockNewsTimes and is the sole property of of StockNewsTimes. If you are reading this news story on another website, it was illegally stolen and republished in violation of USA and worldwide copyright and trademark law. The correct version of this news story can be accessed at https://www.thecerbatgem.com/2017/07/25/hawaiian-telcom-holdco-inc-nasdaqhcom-position-cut-by-ameriprise-financial-inc-updated.html. Sidoti lowered Hawaiian Telcom Holdco from a "buy" rating to a "neutral" rating in a research report on Monday, July 10th. Finally, TheStreet raised shares of Hawaiian Telcom Holdco from a "d+" rating to a "c-" rating in a research note on Wednesday, April 26th.Hawaiian Telcom Holdco does not pay a dividend.




