Size does matter.
See how much of a difference the number of Mbps actually makes.


What are Mbps? And why does it matter?
Mbps stands for megabits per second, and it tells you how fast your web pages will load. How many devices you can use at once. And how much time
				it takes to download music, photos, streaming movies and more. The more Mbps, the better. And with Hawaii’s fastest Internet, you get plenty.
Not big on sharing? We don't blame you.
We can offer you a dedicated Internet line. Because you don’t have to share your Internet pipeline, the speed will be better. And that’s a very good thing. 





